    <!-- Security & Compliance Section -->
    <section class="security">
        <div class="container">
            <h2 class="section-heading">AI You Can Trust. Standards You Can Verify.</h2>
            <p class="security-intro">Implementing AI in government requires more than capability. It requires compliance, transparency, and documentation that procurement can defend. Every AI system we deploy comes with the security framework and audit trail your agency requires.</p>

            <div class="security-grid">
                <div class="security-item">
                    <div class="security-icon"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M12 2L4 6v5c0 5.55 3.84 10.74 8 12 4.16-1.26 8-6.45 8-12V6l-8-4z" stroke="#FF5833" stroke-width="2" fill="none"/></svg></div>
                    <h4>CCPA / CPRA Compliant</h4>
                    <p>Data handling practices aligned with California Consumer Privacy Act and California Privacy Rights Act. Documented procedures for data subject requests, retention, and deletion.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="security-item">
                    <div class="security-icon"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><rect x="3" y="11" width="18" height="11" rx="2" stroke="#FF5833" stroke-width="2"/><path d="M7 11V7a5 5 0 0110 0v4" stroke="#FF5833" stroke-width="2"/></svg></div>
                    <h4>NIST-Aligned Encryption</h4>
                    <p>Data encrypted in transit and at rest using industry-standard protocols aligned with NIST Cybersecurity Framework. No unencrypted data storage.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="security-item">
                    <div class="security-icon"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><circle cx="12" cy="8" r="4" stroke="#FF5833" stroke-width="2"/><path d="M4 20c0-4 4-6 8-6s8 2 8 6" stroke="#FF5833" stroke-width="2"/></svg></div>
                    <h4>Role-Based Access Controls</h4>
                    <p>Access enforced at the data layer. Admins see everything. Department staff see only their data. Every access event logged by user, timestamp, and action.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="security-item">
                    <div class="security-icon"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M9 5H7a2 2 0 00-2 2v12a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2V7a2 2 0 00-2-2h-2" stroke="#FF5833" stroke-width="2"/><rect x="9" y="3" width="6" height="4" rx="1" stroke="#FF5833" stroke-width="2"/><path d="M9 14l2 2 4-4" stroke="#FF5833" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg></div>
                    <h4>Full Audit Trail</h4>
                    <p>Every query, report, upload, and form submission is time-stamped and logged. Complete documentation chain. Export-ready for compliance reviews and audits.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="security-item">
                    <div class="security-icon"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M4 19.5A2.5 2.5 0 016.5 17H20" stroke="#FF5833" stroke-width="2"/><path d="M6.5 2H20v20H6.5A2.5 2.5 0 014 19.5v-15A2.5 2.5 0 016.5 2z" stroke="#FF5833" stroke-width="2"/></svg></div>
                    <h4>FERPA-Aware Architecture</h4>
                    <p>Data segmentation and access controls designed to support FERPA compliance for education institutions managing student records and program outcomes.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="security-item">
                    <div class="security-icon"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v16a2 2 0 002 2h12a2 2 0 002-2V8l-6-6z" stroke="#FF5833" stroke-width="2"/><path d="M14 2v6h6M16 13H8M16 17H8M10 9H8" stroke="#FF5833" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg></div>
                    <h4>SOW Documentation Provided</h4>
                    <p>Standard scope of work, implementation milestones, and deliverable schedules provided with every engagement. Procurement receives exactly what they need to process the contract.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

